South Asian, Chinese New Yorkers among the hardest hit by Covid, study shows

legacy.description: News updates from around the 🌎, all day, every day.

legacy.full_text:
In NYC, Chinese patients had the HIGHEST mortality rate of all ethnic and racial groups.

South Asians, the highest positivity & mortality rate amongst Asian Americans.  Their mortality rate second to only Black New Yorkers. 

We need disaggregated data. 

https://t.co/IUYhTG6VvV

The Asian American community cannot be treated as a monolith. Chinese and South Asian New Yorkers have had some of the highest Covid mortality rates but have been largely over looked by public health outreach. 
 
It’s time for leadership that reflects the diversity of NYC.
